<FONT SIZE="2" face="arial,helvetica">
<h4>
	Minutes from ACE-grid BoF at GGF3 on the AccessGrid

</h4></FONT>
<i>	October 19, 2001</i>
<ul>
<pre> 
website: http://calder.ncsa.uiuc.edu/ACE-grid
elist: ace-grid@gridforum.org

This was the first ACE-grid meeting conducted over the 
AccessGrid. Nine (9) remote sites connected to the
Full Sail Room Virtual Venue. One sites from Germany
connected vis H32x via the ACCESS H32x conference server.
The meeting was international in scope.
Remote sites included:

    EVL
    ANL
    ACCESS
    BU
    NCAR
    Manchester
    Amsterdam
    LBNL
    Germany

---
Topics covered:
Slides for the Agenda found here: <a href="http://calder.ncsa.uiuc.edu/ACE-grid/2001-10-19_GGF3/Agenda_ACE_GGF3.ppt">Agenda_ACE_GGF3.ppt</a>
Slides for ACE-grid evolving into a Research Group
found here: <a href="http://calder.ncsa.uiuc.edu/ACE-grid/2001-10-19_GGF3/ACE_Research_Group.ppt">ACE_Research_Group.ppt</a>

The following presenters gave 5 minute briefings: 
<ul>
     <li type="disc">Keith R Jackson [KRJackson@lbl.gov] - <a href="http://calder.ncsa.uiuc.edu/ACE-grid/2001-10-19_GGF3/GCE.ppt">Grid Computing Environments WG</a> 

     <li>Al Gilman [asgilman@iamdigex.net] - <a href="http://calder.ncsa.uiuc.edu/ACE-grid/2001-10-19_GGF3/GPA.ppt">Grid Protocol Architecture</a>

     <li>Andre Merzky [merzky@zib.de] - DATA working groups 

     <li>Mary Thompson [mrthompson@lbl.gov] - <a href="http://calder.ncsa.uiuc.edu/ACE-grid/2001-10-19_GGF3/security.ppt">Security WG</a> 

</ul>
---
Interests:
    EVL
	Security
	Events
    
    ANL
	Security
	Resource Discovery
    
    Manchester (Reality Grid, Grid Lab)
	GrdiFTP
	Security
    
    Nottingham
	Security
    
    Mary Anne Scott - DOE
	Science Grid
	work at University of Indiana

</pre>        
</ul>




